"Zhou G., Huang H., Dong Z., Yu Z.","Temporal stability of Symbiodinium phylotype in scleractinian coral Galaxea fascicularis from a tropical fringing reef in the South China Sea",2011,"Chinese Journal of Oceanology and Limnology","29","6",,"1186","1191",,,10.1007/s00343-011-0301-6,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-80155130670&partnerID=40&md5=0dbea6017f2cf0d493b9691210a13cae","Key Laboratory of Marine Bio-Resources Sustainable Utilization, South China Sea Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Guangzhou 510301, China; Yantai Institute of Coastal Zone Research, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Yantai 264003, China; Tropical Marine Biological Research Station in Hainan, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Sanya 572000, China; Graduate University of Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100049, China","Zhou, G., Key Laboratory of Marine Bio-Resources Sustainable Utilization, South China Sea Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Guangzhou 510301, China, Tropical Marine Biological Research Station in Hainan, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Sanya 572000, China, Graduate University of Chinese Academy of Sciences, Beijing 100049, China; Huang, H., Key Laboratory of Marine Bio-Resources Sustainable Utilization, South China Sea Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Guangzhou 510301, China, Tropical Marine Biological Research Station in Hainan, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Sanya 572000, China; Dong, Z., Yantai Institute of Coastal Zone Research, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Yantai 264003, China; Yu, Z., Key Laboratory of Marine Bio-Resources Sustainable Utilization, South China Sea Institute of Oceanology, Chinese Academy of Sciences, Guangzhou 510301, China","Symbiodinium sp. occurs in a symbiotic association with various marine invertebrates, including the scleractinian corals. Understanding the flexibility and specificity in coral-algal symbiosis can have important implications for predicting the future of coral reefs in the era of global climate change. In the present study, we conducted Symbiodinium phylotype analysis, based on polymerase chain reaction and restriction fragment length polymorphism (PCR-RFLP), in the scleractinian coral, Galaxea fascicularis, from a tropical fringing reef in Hainan Island, over a 1-yr period. Our results showed that Galaxea fascicularis could associate with Symbiodinium clade C and D either individually or simultaneously. However, during the sampling period, the Symbiodinium phylotype did not change significantly in the scleractinian coral Galaxea fascicularis, although the seawater temperature decreased sharply in the winter season. This study further suggests that the shift in Symbiodinium communities in response to seasonally fluctuating environments might not be a universal feature of coral-algal associations. © 2011 Chinese Society for Oceanology and Limnology, Science Press and Springer-Verlag Berlin Heidelberg.","coral; South China Sea; Symbiodinium; symbiosis","algae; Anthozoa; Galaxea fascicularis; Invertebrata; Scleractinia; Symbiodinium; Symbiodinium sp.",,,,,,"Baker, A.C., Ecosystems - reef corals bleach to survive change (2001) Nature, 411, pp. 765-766; Baker, A.C., Flexibility and specificity in coral-algal symbiosis: Diversity, ecology, and biogeography of Symbiodinium. (2003) Annu. Rev. Ecol. Evol. S., 34, pp. 661-689; Berkelmans, R., Oliver, J.K., Large-scale bleaching of corals on the Great Barrier Reef (1999) Coral Reefs, 18, pp. 55-60; Berkelmans, R., van Oppen, M.J.H., The role of zooxanthellae in the thermal tolerance of corals: A 'nugget of hope' for coral reefs in an era of climate change (2006) P. Roy. Soc. B-Biol. Sci., 273, pp. 2305-2312; Brown, B.E., Dunne, R.P., Warner, M.E., Ambarsari, I., Fitt, W.K., Gibb, S.W., Cummings, D.G., Damage and recovery of photosystem II during a manipulative field experiment on solar bleaching in the coral Goniastrea aspera (2000) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 195, pp. 117-124; Buddemeier, R.W., Fautin, D.G., Coral bleaching as an adaptive mechanism-a testable hypothesis (1993) Bioscience, 43, pp. 320-326; Chen, C.A., Yu, J.K., Universal primers for amplification of mitochondrial small subunit ribosomal RNA-encoding gene in scleractinian corals (2000) Mar. Biotech., 2, pp. 146-153; Chen, C.A., Wang, A.T., Fang, L.S., Yang, Y.W., Fluctuating algal symbiont communities in Acropora palifera (scleractinia: Acroporidae) from Taiwan (2005) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 295, pp. 113-121; Diekmann, O.E., Bak, R.P.M., Tonk, L., Stam, W.T., Olsen, J.L., No habitat correlation of zooxanthellae in the coral genus Madracis on a Curacao reef (2002) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 227, pp. 221-232; Dong, Z.J., Huang, H., Huang, L.M., Li, Y.C., Diversity of symbiotic algae of the genus Symbiodinium in scleractinian corals of the Xisha Islands in the South China Sea (2009) J. Syst. Evol., 47, pp. 321-326; Douglas, A.E., Coral bleaching - how and why? (2003) Mar. Pollut. Bull., 46, pp. 385-392; Freudenthal, H.D., Symbiodinium gen. nov. and Symbiodinium microadriaticum sp. nov, a zooxanthellataxonomy, life cycle, and morphology (1962) J. Protozool., 9, pp. 45-52; Glynn, P.W., Coral reef bleaching: Facts, hypotheses and implications (1996) Glob. Change Biol., 2, pp. 495-509; Glynn, P.W., Mate, J.L., Baker, A.C., Calderon, M.O., Coral bleaching and mortality in Panama and Ecuador during the 1997-1998 El Niño-Southern Oscillation Event: Spatial/temporal patterns and comparisons with the 1982-1983 event (2001) B. Mar. Sci., 69, pp. 79-109; Goulet, T.L., Most corals may not change their symbionts (2006) Mar. Ecol. Prog. Ser., 321, pp. 1-7; Goulet, T.L., Lajeunesse, T.C., Fabricius, K.E., Symbiont specificity and bleaching susceptibility among soft corals in the 1998 Great Barrier Reef mass coral bleaching event (2008) Mar. Biol., 154, pp. 795-804; Hoegh-Guldberg, O., Salvat, B., Periodic mass-bleaching and elevated sea temperatures bleaching of outer reef slope communities in Moorea, French-Polynes